# Implement Authentication System

Implement a login interface that authenticates users via the hospital's `HISLogin` service and manages sessions to enable secure data retrieval and deep linking.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend (Flask)

#### [MODIFY] [app.py](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/app.py)
- Add `/login` and `/logout` routes.
- Integrate `flask-session` to store authenticated user credentials (`SignOnID`, `CreateID`, etc.).
- Protect existing routes (`/`, `/api/*`) to require an active session.
- Update data fetching logic to use the authenticated user's ID instead of the hardcoded `A03772`.

#### [NEW] [auth_handler.py](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/auth_handler.py)
- Implement `validate_user(username, password)` calling `http://10.10.246.80/Ipo/HISLogin/CheckUserByID`.

#### [MODIFY] [his_client_final.py](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/his_client_final.py)
- Update [HISClient](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/his_api_client.py#3-61) and its methods to accept a `current_user` ID and patch binary templates dynamically with this ID.

### Frontend

#### [NEW] [login.html](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/templates/login.html)
- A premium, modern login page with hospital branding.
- Fields for Username/ID and Password.

#### [MODIFY] [index.html](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/templates/index.html)
- Add a "Logout" button and display the current logged-in user's name.

#### [MODIFY] [legacy_schedule.html](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/templates/legacy_schedule.html)
- Dynamically populate the IPD links using the `SignOnID` and `CreateID` (encrypted password) stored in the session.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Test `/api/login` with valid and invalid credentials.
- Verify that accessing `/` without a session redirects to `/login`.

### Manual Verification
- Log in as a authorized user and verify that surgery lists and patient details are retrieved correctly.
- Click on an "Inpatient Record" link and verify it opens the external HIS system with the correct authenticated session.
